Azure Key Vault CSI driver using Helm:
1️⃣ Add the repo (if not already)
helm repo add csi-secrets-store-provider-azure https://azure.github.io/secrets-store-csi-driver-provider-azure/charts

2️⃣ Update the repo index
helm repo update

3️⃣ Confirm the chart name
helm search repo csi-secrets-store-provider-azure --output json

You should see something like:
NAME                                                      CHART VERSION   APP VERSION DESCRIPTION
csi-secrets-store-provider-azure/secrets-store-csi-driver-provider-azure  1.2.3          0.0.23     Azure Key Vault CSI driver
Note the chart version (optional; you can install a specific version with --version).

4️⃣ Install the chart
helm install csi-secrets-store-provider-azure csi-secrets-store-provider-azure/csi-secrets-store-provider-azure --namespace kube-system --create-namespace


🔹 csi-secrets-store-provider-azure → release name
🔹 csi-secrets-store-provider-azure/secrets-store-csi-driver-provider-azure → chart name
🔹 --namespace kube-system → install into kube-system
🔹 --create-namespace → creates the namespace if it doesn’t exist

5️⃣ Verify installation
helm list -n kube-system
kubectl get pods -n kube-system | grep csi
You should see DaemonSet pods running for the CSI driver.
